      "id": "GENUS_DASYPUS",
      "name": "Dasypus",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Nine-banded armadillos — the only armadillo with a substantial range in North America and the only armadillo that regularly crosses the USA-Mexico border (it has expanded northward to Nebraska and North Carolina since the 19th century). Nine-banded armadillos are notable for two remarkable biological facts: they always give birth to identical quadruplets (from a single fertilised egg that divides four times), and they are the only non-human animal known to naturally carry Mycobacterium leprae, the bacterium that causes leprosy — human cases in southern USA have been traced to contact with wild armadillos. They are also excellent swimmers, inflating their intestines to become buoyant, or alternatively walking along the bottom of rivers.",
