      "id": "GENUS_TOLYPEUTES",
      "name": "Tolypeutes",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Three-banded armadillos — the only armadillos able to roll into a complete, sealed ball. Most armadillos protect themselves by digging rapidly into the ground; three-banded armadillos occupy drier, harder-substrate habitats where digging is impractical, and instead evolved a perfectly spherical defensive posture with no gaps. The shell plates fit together so precisely that even a prying human hand struggles to open them. The southern three-banded armadillo is the mascot of the 2014 FIFA World Cup (Fuleco). Both species are native to South America's Cerrado and Caatinga.",
