      "id": "GENUS_CHLAMYPHORUS",
      "name": "Chlamyphorus",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "The pink fairy armadillo — the world's smallest armadillo and one of the most bizarre mammals. At just 90–115 mm long, it is the size of a large hamster. Its shell is paper-thin and attached to the spine only by a membrane along the dorsal midline, making it far more flexible than other armadillos. The shell is also pink, reflecting a rich blood supply that allows the animal to thermoregulate by flushing blood through it. The fairy armadillo is a sand-swimmer — it burrows through loose, sandy soil with remarkable speed, essentially swimming underground. Rarely seen and almost impossible to keep in captivity, it remains very poorly known.",
